RACE.RACE_TEXT: HAWTHORNE RACE 1 5F Dirt CR: 76. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners of a race since March 9 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000 (Claiming races for $12,500 or less not considered in es timating allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: IT'S GREEK TO ME set the pace inside facing some early pressured, edged away leaving the turn while coming off the fence a bit, drew away in the stretch and was kept to the task with moderate hand-urging. OCEAN HONEY pressed the eventual winner from between runners two to three wide into the turn, was no match for the top one but held the place. MUD HUT pursued from in behind the leading trio into the turn racing off the fence in about the three path, moved out wider for the drive, kept on in the lane but missed second. SWEET FRAULEIN broke a half-step slowly and was forced in at the start, lacked early speed despite some encouragement, moved out three to four deep before the turn, swung seven wide into the stretch and ran on with mild late interest. FROST WARRIOR broke inwardly, was forwardly-positioned briefly then chased while dropping back racing near the inside, failed to make a late bid. CESSO pursued the leader just off that one's flank racing outside three to four wide, steadily weakened.

ENTRY.NAME: It's Greek to Me
ENTRY.COMMENT: pace, inside/off rail, drew away, kept to task, moderate urging

ENTRY.NAME: Sweet Fraulein
ENTRY.COMMENT: 1/2 step slow & forced in brk, no speed, 3-4p, swung 7w, mildly

ENTRY.NAME: Frost Warrior
ENTRY.COMMENT: brk in, brief chase, dropped back, near inside, no late bid

ENTRY.NAME: Ocean Honey
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed winner, 2-3wide, held 2nd

ENTRY.NAME: Cesso
ENTRY.OWNER: Morgan Sharon R and Mineer Pat
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3-4w pursuit, weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Mud Hut
ENTRY.COMMENT: in behind, 3path turn, kept on, missed place

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HAWTHORNE RACE 2 5F Dirt CR: 71. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners of a race since February 9 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250 (Claiming races for $4,000 or less not considered in estimating allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TAP N TWINE raced off the leading pair in about the three path into the turn, still had a bit to do by the top of the stretch but took aim, gained steadily then surged pats late to get up in time under steady handling. SMILE AT THE STORM appeared to brush the gate lightly but was still close up attending the pace from outside soon after racing two to three wide, took closer order to contest the issue late on the turn, struck the lead in upper stretch, was asked past the three-sixteenths, responded by edging clear of dueling partner but was outkicked by the winner. NIFF was urged at the start and quickly took the lead to set the pace, was pressured into the turn racing inside, dueled with a rival, yielded grudgingly late. IRISH HALO settled off the pace, raced outside a foe two wide through the turn off the leaders, was never near enough to threaten. ZENCHUA SKY chased very briefly, dropped back inside and was unable to threaten.

ENTRY.NAME: Niff
ENTRY.OWNER: RSR Racing Services LLC (Robert S Rhoads)
ENTRY.COMMENT: urged brk, pace, dueled, yielded grudgingly

ENTRY.NAME: Smile At the Storm
ENTRY.COMMENT: hit gate, attended pace 2-3w, led upper, ask past 3/16, outkicked

ENTRY.NAME: Zenchua Sky
ENTRY.COMMENT: brief chase, dropped back inside, outpaced, no threat

ENTRY.NAME: Tap N Twine
ENTRY.COMMENT: off pair, 3path turn, surged past, up in time

ENTRY.NAME: Irish Halo
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled, 2wide & outside rival, no threat

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HAWTHORNE RACE 3 5F Dirt CR: 98. Starter Allowance Purse 17000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $6,250 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners of a race since February 9 Allowed 2 lbs. (Claiming races for $6,250 or less not considered in estimating allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SILVER MOON ROAD broke on top to set the early pace inside, was pressured into the turn, asked for run at the three-sixteenths, maintained a narrow lead to the wire holding off rivals while being kept to the task. DARK HEDGES was slightly fractious in the gate, bumped the inner rival lightly at the start, was forwardly-positioned outside pressing three wide on the turn, kept on in the stretch and saved the place from PERFECT WAGER, who was outsprinted early, raced between runners three wide at the rear through the turn, swung out five wide for the drive, was gaining too late and missed second. SOUPER FORTUNE bobbled slightly and was lightly bumped into a rival at the start, moved forward between runners to press the leader through the turn, weakened in the stretch. TRY TRY AGAIN was lightly bumped at the start, gave brief chase then dropped back racing in the two path through the turn, was unable to menace. D'FEVER raced at the rear four wide on the turn, swung six to seven deep into upper stretch and failed to rally.

ENTRY.NAME: Silver Moon Road
ENTRY.COMMENT: pace, inside, pressured, ask 3/16, held foes

ENTRY.NAME: Try Try Again
ENTRY.COMMENT: light bump brk, brief foot, dropped back, 2path turn, no menace

ENTRY.NAME: Souper Fortune
ENTRY.COMMENT: bobbled, light bumps brk, pressed btwn, weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Dark Hedges
ENTRY.COMMENT: slightly fractious gate, light bump brk, pressed 3wide, kept on

ENTRY.NAME: Perfect Wager
ENTRY.OWNER: Ritter Charles W and Becker Scott
ENTRY.COMMENT: outsprinted, 3wd btwn turn, gaining too late, missed 2nd

ENTRY.NAME: D'fever
ENTRY.COMMENT: 4wide turn, swung 6-7w, no rally

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HAWTHORNE RACE 4 5F Dirt CR: 76. Maiden Special Weight Purse 30000. FOR ILLINOIS REGISTERED, CONCEIVED AND/OR FOALED. Maidens, Three Years Old and Upward. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FEVER NATION broke inwardly just a bit, quickly moved clear under mild early coaxing, dictated terms on or just off the rail in the clear, was unasked till mid-stretch then responded by drawing away. INSIDE THE CIRCLE got away alertly but was soon overtaken. chased the winner two to three wide, was no match and just saved the place from DASH TO THE CASH, who was lightly brushed at the start, settled at the back racing off the inside, went about three wide on the turn, kept on late but just missed second. NAGY AND DA BEARS chased briefly but soon steadily dropped back two wide, offered no late bid. MAN ON ATTACK was ridden from the break, chased outside going three to four wide on the turn, failed to rally. IRISH BRUTE lacked early speed racing inside early, failed to threaten.

ENTRY.COMMENT: no speed, inside early, no threat

ENTRY.COMMENT: brief chase, dropped back 2wide, no late bid

ENTRY.COMMENT: brk in bit, moved clear, asked mid-str, drew away

ENTRY.COMMENT: away alertly, chased winner 2-3w, saved place

ENTRY.NAME: Man On Attack
ENTRY.COMMENT: ridden break, chased outside, 3-4wide turn, no rally

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HAWTHORNE RACE 5 5F Dirt CR: 69. Claiming Purse 10500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES IN 2022 - 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE MARCH 9, 2022. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners of a race since February 9 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Claiming races for $4,000 or less not considered in eligibility and allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HOPPESTRY raced off the leading pair into the turn, went in the three path on that bend, angled outside the leaders in upper stretch six deep, took aim and drove past late under steady urging. FIRST SQUADRON was urged forward at the break, prompted the pace from outside three to four wide, dueled in upper stretch, outbattled that rival late but was outkicked by the winner and just held second. FRIEND was mid-pack off the leaders and outside a rival four deep into the turn, swung seven to eight wide for the drive, was gaining too late and missed the place. FOGGY KITTEN got away alertly, was challenged up the backstretch, attended then dueled inside that rival, drifted out turning for home, was asked just past the quarter pole but outkicked. SINGING ALLI chased briefly inside, dropped back a bit, saved ground through the turn gaining on the leaders into upper stretch then went evenly. WANNA HAVE FUN broke awkwardly and a couple lengths slowly, raced at the back off the inside and was not a factor. GODSGIFT was outpaced and never a threat.

ENTRY.COMMENT: urged forward, prompted pace 3-4w, outkicked, held 2nd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HAWTHORNE RACE 6 5F Dirt CR: 75. Maiden Special Weight Purse 30000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (Preference by condition eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WAR ROOM stalked the loose leader three wide, advanced on that one leaving the turn and into upper stretch, was getting in badly through the stretch, hooked up and dueled, exchanged a light bump late and edged past. ONASA sped clear under mild early coaxing, set the pace racing off the fence, was asked in mid-stretch when engaged by an outside rival, was a bit crowded by that rival, exchanged a light bump late and was outfinished. LIGHTNING CASHES was ridden at the break, chased inside, proved no match for the top pair. FITZEA raced outside a rival four to five wide through the turn and was unable to menace. YOLO SANTIAGO lacked early speed, switched well off the inside early, raced inside a foe but in about the three path on the turn and was never near enough to threaten. FOLLOWING AN OBJECTION BY THE TRAINER OF ONASA AGAINST WAR ROOM ALLEGING INTERFERENCE IN THE STRETCH, NO ACTION WAS TAKEN.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SOVIET STANDARD exchanged a bump at the start, stalked from outside mid-pack, advanced four wide on the turn, struck the lead at the top of the stretch, forged clear under moderate urging.
